Today let’s talk about flowers. My favorite flower is the lavender because it smells really nice and it is calming. What’s yours?
Let’s create a list of my favorite flowers using python:
import numpy as np flowers=np.array([&quot;lavender&quot;,&quot;daisy&quot;,&quot;sunflower&quot;,&quot;lotus&quot;]) Oh but I also like wisteria! Let’s add that in using R:
library(reticulate) py$flowers[5]&lt;-&quot;wisteria&quot; py$flowers ## [1] &quot;lavender&quot; &quot;daisy&quot; &quot;sunflower&quot; &quot;lotus&quot; &quot;wisteria&quot;
